---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="tag-accent">Engineering · Computer Vision · Robotics · Physics-informed Modeling</p>
    <h1>吴润裕 / Ryen Wu</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Building intelligent systems that connect neural networks with the physical world,
      from leaf spectral trait inversion to real-time robotic vision and navigation.
    </p>
    <p class="intro" style="font-size: 17px; margin-top: 12px;">
      5+ Robotics / Vision Projects
      30 FPS Embedded YOLO Deployment
      PROSPECT-PRO / PI-NN Research
      ROS / SLAM / RKNN Experience
    </p>
    <div class="btn-group">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + '/projects'} class="btn">View Projects</a>
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + '/research'} class="btn">Research</a>
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + '/cv.pdf'} class="btn">Download CV</a>
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + '/contact'} class="btn">Contact Me</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-title">Featured Research</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Leaf Spectral Trait Inversion</h3>
      <p>
        A physics-informed learning framework for estimating leaf traits such as
        Cab, Car, Cw, Prot, and CBC from spectral data. Combines PROSPECT-PRO
        radiative transfer modeling with neural encoder-decoder architectures.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Encoder-Decoder Architecture Exploration</h3>
      <p>
        Exploring CNN, Transformer, VAE, Gated Residual, and Pair-relation encoder
        structures for VIS-NIR-SWIR spectral representation learning, with
        physics-informed decoders for improved reliability and interpretability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="section-title">Engineering Projects</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Autonomous Robot Navigation and Target Recognition</h3>
      <p>
        Designed task-switching logic between long-distance exploration and close-range
        YOLOv5-based visual navigation. Participated in navigation strategy design and
        assisted in building the autonomous robot system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Outdoor Smart Car Vision System</h3>
      <p>
        Deployed YOLOv3-tiny for obstacle and speed bump detection on embedded devices,
        achieving real-time inference at ~30 FPS for smart car outdoor race tasks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + '/projects'}>View all projects →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
